reviews.title: Awesome small chest freezer
reviews.review_text: We purchased this through the app at our local Wal-Mart. We wanted a small chest freezer for frozen foods storage, and this one is perfect. Sometimes delivery services such as UPS or FedEx aren't exactly gentle with their deliveries. A Wal-Mart employee was able to fit it in the back of my Chevy Blazer without any problem.

Perfect size for a small one bedroom apartment. Very very quiet, you don't even know it's running. I really like the light indicator on the outside to assure me it's on and the basket it comes with. Best investment I've ever made! I have saved so much money buying larger bulk items vs. weekly groceries knowing the food keeps longer than your traditional refrigerator freezer.

reviews.title: I love my FREEZER Five Stars! ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
reviews.review_text: Five Stars! ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ I absolutely LOVE my deep freezer! As a small business owner running a home bakery, this is goaded for me. I definitely needed the extra freezer space, and it did not disappoint. I’ve seen so many bad reviews about dents and damages, so I was nervous. But let me tell you—mine arrived in perfect condition. No dents, no scratches, nothing. It even came super fast! I ordered mine at 2 a.m., and it was delivered by 10 a.m. the same day. I wasn’t even expecting it until later that night, so that was a pleasant surprise. If you’re debating whether to buy this—buy it! Run and get it. It gets cold fast. I turned mine on, and within 30 minutes, it was already really cold. It has different settings (minimum, mid, and max), and of course, I set mine to max because I need my treats frozen solid. The size is perfect. It’s actually bigger than I expected—about 4 feet wide and 3.5 feet tall—so there’s plenty of space. It also comes with a small tray at the top, which is perfect for organizing. I added small bins inside to keep my treats separate from my regular food, which helps keep everything organized and clean. The price? $165. I hesitate to spend over $100 on anything, but this was worth it. You also get a one-year warranty, so make sure to fill out that paperwork! And let’s be real—who wants to haul a freezer home from the store when Walmart delivers it for free once you spend over $35? I know how hard it is to find honest reviews because some people just love to bash companies, making it impossible to tell if something is actually good or not. But this is my honest experience, and I hope this helps someone who’s been debating like I was. I’ll update this review in a week, but so far—five stars all the way!

reviews.title: Great freezer, but BAD CHEMICAL OFF-GASSING
reviews.review_text: The freezer works fine once set up, but I need to warn people: when I first opened it in my garage (before even plugging it in), I was blasted with the worst chemical offgassing I've ever experienced. Didn't expect a literal wall of VOCs to hit me in the face. One deep breath and immediately I had issues breathing. It persisted days after. I'm a young adult, healthy, and don't have asthma or any breathing problems, so for it to have affected me that long shows just how strong the offgassing was. There was no warning label about ventilation. Without airing it out first, all those toxic chemicals just get sealed in with your food. I wouldn't risk that, especially with long-term storage. This is preventable so it's just manufacturing laziness from companies to not air out ahead of time. If you're sensitive to breathing in harmful chemicals, have asthma, or even enjoy breathing, DO NOT open this in a closed room. I recommend letting it sit outside for a full day, wiping everything down, and leaving baking soda trays inside before plugging it in The design's solid for the price, but zero points for user safety or transparency. Would be 5 stars if they included an offgassing warning at the very least, but really customers should not have to worry about this.

reviews.title: Buyer Beware
reviews.review_text: My freezer was delivered in an SUV and left in my driveway upside down. No one rang my doorbell. They just dropped it off and left. I would of called them to come pick it back up if there was any damage to the box, but the box had no imperfections at all so I figured I had received an undamaged product. NOT SO. My husband was out of town for a couple of weeks so I was unable to open it for awhile and took another week so he could run a direct electric line to it. Once opened, it had a large dent that went from the front to the side. How could this happen with a perfectly unmarred box? Is the company taking their returns and reboxing them?? I looked all over for a phone number to call Walmart to lodge my complaint, but all you can talk to is a computer and there is no area to talk about damages. Will this dent void the extra warranty I paid for from Walmart? I went ahead and plugged it in and have monitored the temperature for 2 weeks now and it seems to be running fine even with the dent. I don't really care about the dent as the freezer is in a place that only the family can see, but I do believe I am due a discount due to the damage. Should I have to pay full price for a damaged freezer? I like the freezer. It is the perfect size for us so I gave only 3 stars due to the way it was delivered by Walmart and because of the manufacturer's attempt at trying to hide the damage by reboxing.
